        <h1 itemprop="headline">Evolving My Projects: From WodiWebify to WodiNotes</h1>
        <p><strong>📅 Published on:</strong> <time datetime="2025-08-26" itemprop="datePublished">August 26, 2025</time></p>
        <p><strong>✍️ Written by:</strong> <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name">Caleb Chikanka Wodi</span></span></p>
      </header>

      <section itemprop="articleBody
          <img src="wodinotes-logo.png" alt="WodiNotes Logo" />

        <p>As a founder, one of the most interesting parts of building a project isn’t just the coding, designing, or marketing—it’s the journey of naming, branding, and evolving it.</p>

        <p>Today, I’m sharing a small but important change: WodiWebify is now WodiNotes.</p>

        <p>When I first started WodiWebify, the name felt right. But over time, I realized it didn’t fully capture what the platform truly is: an encrypted, secure note-taking app designed to keep your thoughts, ideas, and reflections private and organized.</p>

        <p>Changing a project name isn’t easy. You worry about recognition, consistency, and even how your audience—or in this case, Google—will perceive it. But clarity matters. WodiNotes communicates exactly what we do, and that makes it easier for people to find, understand, and trust the platform.</p>

        <p>Rest assured—your notes and experience stay exactly the same. This is just an evolution in how we present ourselves to the world. To honor the past, I’m noting that this is “formerly WodiWebify.”</p>

        <p>Building projects is all about learning, adapting, and making decisions that align with your vision—even if it means letting go of something familiar. For me, this is one of those moments.</p>

        <p>And here’s a little tease: what was going to be WodiWebify v2 is now WodiNotes v2, launching soon. It’s the next step in making your encrypted note-taking experience even better—more intuitive, faster, and smarter.</p>

        <p>I’ll continue sharing my journey here on WodiWideWeb, documenting every decision, reflection, and memory along the way. And yes—there will be more evolutions, more lessons, and more Wodi-brand moments.</p>

        <p>Here’s to building, growing, and always moving closer to the vision.</p>

        <p>— Caleb Chikanka Wodi</p>
